The paper discusses the cognitive mechanisms, knowledge, and representations involved in code reuse activity performed by experienced programmers. This topic is closely related to software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it involves the design and development of software. The paper also mentions the use of reasoning and analogies, which are topics in programming languages (cs.PL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
